  "prompt": "What's a good uninstalled for windows?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a good uninstaller for Windows, here are a few popular options that you can consider:\n\n1. **Revo Uninstaller**: This tool not only uninstalls programs but also scans for leftover files, folders, and registry entries after the uninstallation process. It offers both a free and a paid version with more advanced features.\n\n2. **IObit Uninstaller**: This user-friendly uninstaller removes programs along with their residual files. It also offers features like batch uninstallation and a tool to remove stubborn software.\n\n3. **Geek Uninstaller**: A lightweight and portable application that provides a simple interface for uninstalling software. It also includes a \"Force Uninstall\" feature for stubborn programs and a scan for leftover files.\n\n4. **Bulk Crap Uninstaller**: This is a free and open-source tool that excels at removing multiple programs quickly. It also includes options for scanning for leftover files and a user-friendly interface.\n\n5. **Wise Program Uninstaller**: This is another free tool that allows for a standard and advanced uninstallation. It can help remove unwanted software and its traces effectively.\n\n6. **Windows Built-in Uninstaller**: Don\u2019t forget that Windows itself has a built-in uninstallation feature. You can access it via Settings > Apps > Apps & features. While less powerful than third-party options, it\u2019s always available without any extra installation.\n\nConsider trying a few of these to see which one suits your needs best!",
